          "lecture_id": "differential_equations_001",
          "span": "Heun's method extends the forward Euler method with a predictor-corrector step."
        },
        {
          "lecture_id": "differential_equations_001",
          "span": "It first forms the Euler predictor\n\n\\[\n\\widetilde{y}_{n+1} = y_n + hF(t_n,y_n),\n\\]\n\nthen averages the slope at the current point with the slope at the predicted point. The corrected update is\n\n\\[\ny_{n+1} = y_n + \\frac{h}{2}\\left(F(t_n,y_n)+F(t_n+h,\\widetilde{y}_{n+1})\\right).\n\\]"
        }
      ],
      "rationale": "Heun's update is a more specific development that builds upon the forward Euler update by adding a predictor-corrector step, preserving the Euler method as its conceptual base."
    }
  ]
